In a day and time where the average Joe gets less and less for FREE and also in a day and time where fewer and fewer of our vacation pics actually end up developed and printed, Binion's in downtown Las Vegas takes care of both needs. A cool souvenir

Located in the back of the casino near the sports book is Benny's Smokin' BBQ and Brews with delicious and affordable BBQ.  Inside the restaurant is a separate enclosed man cave of a room with tvs and leather chairs, devoted to the pleasure of cigar smoking. It is open during restaurant hours and has no cover charge. Drinks can be purchased at restaurant bar. You can bring your own cigars or buy them at nearby Vato's Cigars across the hall. Restaurant opens at 4pm daily.

This magnificent buffet in the Main Street Hotel and Casino downtown is truly one of the best I've had in Vegas for these reasons: 1. The price of this buffet for dinner is absolutely affordable and is of high quality, variety and flavor. It's $12 per person if you don't have a players card, cheaper even so if you do. 2. Most importantly. They offer oxtail stew on certain nights and it is is superb and worth the $12 alone. 
The only knock on this buffet is that they only have Pepsi products.

It has to be at least a little strange. I know that nothing gold can stay. And this also makes me bereft.

During the month of July (2015), the museum will host weekly screenings of cinema noir films mostly from the 1940s and 1950s. Popcorn, soda and other refreshments will be made available at each showing. Check with the museum for further details on specific titles and dates and times of screenings at the museum. How awesome is this? Old black and white gangster films  shown right inside The Mob Museum? Sounds like a cool date thing to do! If I was a Las Vegas citizen, I would be in attendance!
Yo-Yo Ma will perform here December 2, 2016, in a gala concert celebrating the 10th Anniversary of the Montreal Bach Festival. The show will begin at 7:30pm. Tickets are on sale now.

In all seriousness, check this out! Quick and easy, just the way everyone likes it. Delicious savory crepes. Enjoyed the Shrimp Scampi in particular.

Portions are overwhelmingly massive. Just warning you now! Everything is really delicious, from the *Spiked Kiwi Watermelon Lemonade* to the biscuits to the gargantuan *Sage Fried Chicken Benedict.* You won't leave hungry, guaranteed!

The Five Spiced Pork Belly may just be one of my favorite pork belly dishes ever. The flavor is so intense and smooth, and the skin is perfectly crispy. If I go here again, I may consider eating just many of this dish. I would skip the steak.

Delicious restaurant open til 6am. Perfect for those late Vegas nights. The Veggie Pizza has a perfect thin crust and I really dig the pesto sauce. The Mac 'n Cheese is to die for. The Beef Skewers practically melt in your mouth. Definitely satisfying.

Honestly I thought this hotel would be a little douchey, but it's actually very classy and modern. I especially recommend the suites. Spacious and not bad for the price! Consider staying here during your visit to Sin City.
My favorite Cirque show, hands down! So much intensity, passion, and heartfelt emotion.
Kickass pool party. Steve Aoki dropped the beats and had everyone dancing and splashing!
The brunch food is decent albeit a little pricy. The brunch experience is nice though, especially with mimosas, poker tables, and lots of TV's to watch the game.
Bottle service is totally worth it if you want a place to sit down and chill amidst the madness. But be prepared to pay about $650 for a table\/bottle -- this is Vegas after all!

Night swim is super fun. The pool is the perfect way to cool off from the Vegas heat and enjoy dope beats. Ladies: make sure to wear something over your bikini bottom when walking through the hotels to get here. I was stopped by every staff member!
This is one swankified hotel with gorgeous views of the Strip. Surprisingly, offers reasonable prices. Check it out for your next stay.

Wow! Hands down, the best poke I've had on the mainland. So fresh and perfectly prepared. Just can't get enough! Tried *Kulolo Poke* for the first time and it was incredible. It's derived from taro and served warm in a slightly sweet creamy sauce. Noms!
Chill atmosphere, good music, awesome view of the Strip. And they have sangria.
Delicious fried food heaven! The *Garlic Fried Chicken* is sublime.

What is there to do in Vegas during the day?" People always ask me for advice, and I always have the same answer. Pool party! Marquee is a nice venue for a day club, especially with great DJ's spinning. Not a bad way to spend an afternoon. :)
Amazing pre-fixe lunch menu includes a choice of appetizer, entree, and dessert for only $25.15. What an awesome deal for a fine dining experience in Las Vegas with superb food and service.
Wow, best kept secret in Las Vegas. How is it I'd never heard of it before?! It's literally hidden, tucked away in between some other storefronts. Pizza be yummy!

The *Deluxe SORA Ramen* is where it's at! Thick slices of chashu (pork) are gonna fill you right up. Get corn and garlic on the side. Also try the *Otsumami Platter* for very flavorful chashu, egg, and bamboo shoots.

The Fitness crepe with spinach, mushrooms, and mozzarella is quite tasty. If you're looking for a healthy option, the Detoxifier juice is cleansing indeed: apple, kale, celery, beet, lemon, and ginger.

Chipotlified place for pizza! And salad too. The Prosciutto Pizza is mm, perfecto! And I love that I can customize my Kale Salad too. You can eat healthy one last time before you smell the pizzas and say "forget it.
Most relaxing way to wait for a flight. Complimentary services include: light buffet, cocktails, wifi, TV's, office area, and lounge chairs perfect for napping. Sweet!
The Pork Terrine appetizer is delectable, the Porterhouse Steak is tender and juicy, and the Sea Bass divine. Top it off with wonderful service. Well done!
*Carne Asada Fries* are incredibly laden and hearty. Do it. The *Al Pastor Tacos* are also super delicious. Open til 4am!
Awesome Happy Hour from 5-7pm Mon-Sat. Super fresh fish. Recommend the *Cajun Albacore Sashimi* and *Yellowtail Tostada* from the HH menu. The *Flying Fish Roll* is delicious but a little creamy.
The *Steak Sandwich* is really good! Nice ambiance for dinner.

Meaty heaven is right at our fingertips. My two favorites are the Wagyu Beef Cheeks (so tender!) and the Fried Oxtail Steamed Bun (very unique flavor). You should also try the Cotton Candy Foie Gras if you never have.
Great place for Social Hour (happy hour) in Vegas! You'll definitely fill up at a fraction of the price. All the fish is fresh and delicious, and those *Crispy Brussels Sprouts* are mouth-watering.

The Deviled Eggs are awesome as long you're good with dill -- and a LOT of it. Also highly recommend the Chicken 'n' Watermelon 'n' Waffles although the cheese in the waffles is a bit strange. That chicken though and spiced watermelon!
The Shack Stack is pretty darn good. A cheeseburger and shroom burger combined? Oh yeah. Fries are nice and crisp, and the milkshakes are on point.
Wow, airport prices are cray! Paid over $7 for this Hazelnut Blended Coffee drink (almond milk is 99 cents, ugh). So expensive but very delicious.
Delicious, fresh, reasonable prices. Bomb ass food! The *Hainan Chicken Rice* is one of the most popular items and it's not difficult to see why. Tastes so good!
This place is dangerous! The *Original Chicken & Waffles Skillet* is so good. Doused in maple syrup, the chicken is perfectly breaded and the bacon\/cheddar infused waffle is tasty. Enjoy!

Perfect way to start off your day in Las Vegas. Being from San Jose, I was pleasantly surprised with the quality of food. You can't go wrong with the Nem Nuong (grilled pork rolls), Pho, or Shaking Beef.

The perfect late night spot. Thank you Eggslut for providing such satisfying eats at all hours of the night. Open 12 midnight to 7 PM. Delicious *Bacon, Egg & Cheese Sandwich*. The only thing missing is some kind of potato! Like a hash brown IN the sandwich. HINT HINT.
Gotta love the new Taiyaki. Innovative dessert that tastes so good. I'm a huge matcha fan, so I can't get enough of the *Green Tea Taiyaki with green tea custard*

A little pricy for Chinese food, but reasonable considering it's in a casino. Surprisingly delicious and decent quality *Roast Duck Noodle Soup*. The bao is an interesting take and goes well with pork belly.
